    <p>Markets are closed today. Week 12 ended with Nifty at <strong>23,114 (−0.16% week-on-week)</strong> and Sensex at <strong>74,532 (−0.04%)</strong> — numbers that look almost unchanged but hide one of the most volatile weeks of the year. Thursday&#39;s <strong>3.26% crash</strong> on the HDFC Bank chairman&#39;s resignation was the largest single-day fall since the General Election result day on 4 June 2024. INDIAVIX sits at 22.81, gold fell 7.72%, silver 10.80%. Next week: <strong>4-day week</strong> — Thursday 26 March is a holiday (Ram Navami). Back-to-back expiries: Nifty on Tuesday 24 March, Sensex on Wednesday 25 March.</p>
    <p>Today&#39;s Brief is built around two anchor reads: Groww Digest&#39;s deep essay comparing the 1973 oil crisis to today, and Zerodha&#39;s In The Money weekly market metrics. Plus The Ken&#39;s full week recap and Finshots&#39; Sunday curiosity edition.</p>
