    body:`<p>At FTX26, Razorpay demonstrated a Zomato integration: a user orders food by voice and pays without ever opening a checkout page or UPI app. The AI agent handles discovery and the transaction; the payments app is reduced to a backend authentication layer. This is exactly what PhonePe and Google Pay would not want — their front-end position in the payments flow becoming invisible.</p><p>The Ken's story raises the questions that need answering before agentic commerce scales: Who is liable when an AI agent makes a purchase the user didn't intend? How is consent established? How is fraud handled when there's no human at the point of transaction? In addition to this, neutral cross-platform agents — which compare across marketplaces rather than staying within one platform like Zomato — could be even more disruptive by commoditising seller-selection. The Ken covers the full regulatory and trust landscape. Read in full — this is a story that will matter more every quarter.</p>`
