    url:"https://the-ken.com/podcasts/daybreak/indias-lpg-success-story-runs-on-a-two-day-buffer/",
    body:`<p>This Daybreak episode follows directly from Finshots's LPG story last week, which covered how subsidised domestic cylinders are being diverted to restaurants and businesses because the price gap with commercial LPG is too wide. The Ken's podcast asks the upstream question: how did a programme that successfully connected millions of households to clean cooking end up with only a two-day supply buffer?</p><p>The answer is a combination of factors: supply chains built for the pre-disruption world, storage infrastructure not scaled to match the expansion of PMUY connections, and the commercial diversion problem reducing effective domestic supply further. Due to the Iran conflict, this thin buffer is now a genuine vulnerability. Put simply, a programme designed to provide energy access could become an energy security risk. Available on Spotify and Apple Podcasts.</p>`
